## Font Loading

### Current Setup (NPM Packages)

Fonts are imported in `main.tsx` and `.storybook/preview.ts`:

```typescript
// IBM Plex Sans
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/400.css";  // Regular
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/500.css";  // Medium
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/600.css";  // Semibold
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/700.css";  // Bold

// IBM Plex Serif
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-serif/400.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-serif/600.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-serif/700.css";

// IBM Plex Mono
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-mono/400.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-mono/500.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-mono/600.css";
```

### Future Setup (Custom Fonts)

When switching to production fonts:

1. Place font files in `public/fonts/`
2. Add `@font-face` declarations to `globals.css`
3. Update `tailwind.config.ts` font families

## Accessibility

### Font Size Minimums

- ✅ Never go below `text-xs` (12px) for readable text
- ✅ Use `text-sm` (14px) minimum for body content
- ✅ Use `text-base` (16px) for primary content

### Color Contrast

- ✅ Ensure 4.5:1 contrast for normal text
- ✅ Ensure 3:1 contrast for large text (18px+)
- ✅ Use `text-foreground` for primary content
- ✅ Use `text-muted-foreground` for secondary content

### Line Length

- ✅ Keep line length 45-75 characters for optimal readability
- ✅ Use `max-w-prose` (65ch) for long-form content

```tsx
<article className="max-w-prose">
  <p className="text-base">Long-form content...</p>
</article>
```

## Must Follow

1. ✅ Use `font-sans` (default) for UI and body text
2. ✅ Use `font-serif` for decorative headings only
3. ✅ Use `font-mono` for code and technical content
4. ✅ Never hardcode font families beyond sans/serif/mono
5. ✅ Always pair font size with appropriate line height
6. ✅ Use semantic color tokens (text-foreground, text-muted-foreground)
7. ✅ Use font-medium (500) for buttons and labels
8. ✅ Use font-semibold (600) for subheadings
9. ✅ Use font-bold (700) for main headings
10. ✅ Maintain 12px minimum font size for readability
